FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://localhost:3000/api/v1.0

# Smartcar API

Smartcar API provides a generic interface for communicating with vehicles of all models.

## Version [/version]

Current API version

### Get Version [GET]

+ Response 200 (text/plain; charset=utf-8)

        1.0

## Entry Point [/]

### Get Entry Point [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
          "name": "smartcar-api",
          "version": "1.0",
          "links": {
            "vehicles": "/vehicles/:id"
          }
        }

## All Vehicles [/api/v1.0/vehicles]

### Get All (Cached) Vehicles [GET] 

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        [
          {
            "id": "1234",
            "vin": "123123412412",
            "color": "Metallic Silver",
            "doorCount": 4,
            "driveTrain": "v8",
            "links": {
              "url": "/api/v1.0/vehicles/1234",
              "security": "/api/v1.0/vehicles/1234/doors",
              "fuel": "/api/v1.0/vehicles/1234/fuel",
              "battery": "/api/v1.0/vehicles/1234/battery",
              "engine": "/api/v1.0/vehicles/1234/engine"
            }
          }
        ]

## Vehicle [/api/v1.0/vehicles/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: 1234 (string) - Vehicle ID

### Get Vehicle Info [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
          "vin": "1213231",
          "color": "Metallic Silver",
          "doorCount": 4,
          "driveTrain": "v8"
        }

+ Response 404

+ Response 500

## Security [/api/v1.0/vehicles/{id}/doors]

+ Parameters
    + id: 1234 (string) - Vehicle ID

### Get Security [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        [
          {
            "location": "frontLeft",
            "locked": true
          },
          {
            "location": "frontRight",
            "locked": true
          }
        ]

+ Response 404

+ Response 500

